org.kocakosm.pitaya.time

Class Duration

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.kocakosm.pitaya.time.Duration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Duration>

    public final class Duration
extends Object
implements Comparable<Duration>, Serializable
    A duration. Instances of this class are immutable. Implementation note: the duration is stored as milliseconds in a long value, thus some methods on this class are subject to overflow.
    Author:
    Osman KOCAK
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Method Detail

      • valueOf

        public static Duration valueOf(String duration)
        Parses the given duration's String representation into a Duration instance. The given String must be a list of value/unit pairs separated by ' ', '+', '-', '\n', '\t', '\r', '&' or ',' characters or by the "and" String. Values must be integer (either positive or negative) values. Valid units are: "milliseconds", "millisecond", "millis" and "ms" for milliseconds, "seconds", "second", "sec", "secs" and "s" for seconds, "minutes", "minute", "min", "mins" and "m" for minutes, "hours", "hour" and "h" for hours, "days", "day" and "d" for days. Values must be separated from their unit by a whitespace character. Parsing is not case sensitive.
        Parameters:
        duration - the String to parse into a Duration.
        Returns:
        the parsed Duration.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if duration is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if duration can't be parsed.
        ArithmeticException - if the total duration value overflows the storage capacity of this class.
